cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.NI. 

The paper deals with communication systems and information theory, which suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The presence of a malicious adversary also indicates that the paper may fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of an AVC approach and the consideration of memoryless channels suggest that the paper may also be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with communication systems.
